{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/diarrhoea-adults-assessment/background-information/complications/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"c97deb41-e0b2-5403-91f0-22d6aea9f27c","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 1b864d7a-f102-481b-acee-183f13eb2bd8 --><h2>What are the complications?</h2><!-- end field 1b864d7a-f102-481b-acee-183f13eb2bd8 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 46f2da45-7fa7-4a5b-a02d-c4ec1cb69f1d --><!-- begin field 3cc82dd3-c009-40db-9fc3-fb5780f916d1 --><ul><li><strong>In developed countries, diarrhoea is an important cause of morbidity, but it is responsible for relatively few deaths</strong> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-adults-assessment/references/\">Farthing, 2012</a>]<strong>.</strong> <ul><li>Dehydration increases the risk of life-threatening illness and death, particularly in young infants and children, and older people, and in less developed countries [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-adults-assessment/references/\">Farthing, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-adults-assessment/references/\">Shane, 2017</a>].  </li></ul></li><li><strong>Chronic diarrhoea</strong> can negatively impact on quality of life, for example, avoidance of travelling or going to new places where access to toilet facilities may be difficult; and adaptation of food choices to avoid exacerbating diarrhoea [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-adults-assessment/references/\">Dosanjh and Pardi, 2016</a>]. </li><li>For information on the complications occurring as a result of specific infections causing diarrhoea, see the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/gastroenteritis/\">Gastroenteritis</a>.  </li><li>For complications of conditions causing diarrhoea, see the appropriate CKS topic, for example, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/coeliac-disease/\">Coeliac disease</a>, <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/crohns-disease/\">Crohn&#39;s disease</a>, and <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/\">Ulcerative colitis</a>.  </li></ul><!-- end field 3cc82dd3-c009-40db-9fc3-fb5780f916d1 --><!-- end item 46f2da45-7fa7-4a5b-a02d-c4ec1cb69f1d -->","topic":{"id":"6533613a-a6a0-5161-9e6d-cd4ee7e16f85","topicId":"828aa958-94ce-4c08-b7a9-8aae08eb04a1","topicName":"Diarrhoea - adult's assessment","slug":"diarrhoea-adults-assessment","lastRevised":"Last revised in December 2018","chapters":[{"id":"506b2cc6-f0d5-58b3-a742-aed362fa45d5","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9d304716-61b9-596f-b769-d04740407c6e","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"43e53ae4-7fa5-5ace-adb6-471fd5d9ba8b","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"1bd58366-044e-5365-b064-85d9b8f2bd14","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"8791d0e2-fe70-5573-a704-a1dfb542dab0","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"ed95659f-30b3-5441-bb51-cca45f53a32c","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"b9b92fe1-fc7d-5362-8311-314794c89d2e","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"2d13f20d-3413-5949-a1a2-aaf3badf7af8","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"74365bdf-fcf0-5355-bb87-aa2af08c64cb","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"13940020-7a0d-5509-9c45-cc39f56496fd","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"be71d241-6a32-5754-be35-8e0611b8fb22","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":